---
source: src/cli/mod.rs
assertion: db commands report database health without destructive operations
schema:
  status: DbStatusReport
  check: DbCheckReport
  migrations: DbMigrationsReport
contracts:
  - db status reports database existence, size, WAL state, schema version
  - db status returns error field when database not found or unreadable
  - db check runs quick_check or integrity_check based on --full flag
  - db check reports foreign key violations when --fk flag set
  - db check passed:false when integrity issues found
  - db migrations lists applied and pending migrations
  - db migrations filter supports 'all', 'applied', 'pending'
  - db migrations shows compiled vs actual schema version delta
  - no destructive operations (no DELETE, DROP, or data modification)
  - JSON output is machine-parseable with stable field names
  - exit code 0 on successful report (even if issues reported)
evidence:
  - DbStatusReport.database_path
  - DbStatusReport.exists
  - DbStatusReport.schema_version
  - DbStatusReport.needs_migration
  - DbStatusReport.table_row_counts
  - DbCheckReport.check_type
  - DbCheckReport.passed
  - DbCheckReport.integrity_passed
  - DbCheckReport.foreign_key_passed
  - DbMigrationsReport.applied
  - DbMigrationsReport.pending
  - DbMigrationsReport.needs_migration
